{
  "texts": [
    "The prompt gives only the question and context string or \"system string\" that is sent to the conversational model.",
    "Prompts also promote a better alignment of the new task formulation with the pre-training objective, leading to better use of knowledge captured in pre-training.",
    "The closer match also enables a Few-Shot Learning approach [43], especially for tasks with small training datasets; a good prompt can be worth hundreds of labelled data points [58].Few-Shot learning refers to a setting where the model is given one or few examples within th prompt for the task at inference time as conditioning [3], but no model weights are updated [13].",
    "This method employs in-context learning, providing the language model with K instances of contextcompletion pairs, concluding with the target question for evaluation and subsequent answer generation.",
    "The main advantage of few-shots is a major reduction in the need for taskspecific data [13]."
  ]
}